{"id": 6975, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "3", "year": "2016", "session": "16N", "subtopic": "a-2-metals-and-inductively-coupled-plasma-(icp)-spectroscopy", "title": "16N.3.SL.TZ0.4", "topic_id": "a", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>A student wanted to determine the formula of indium sulfate. She applied an electrical current of 0.300A to an aqueous solution of indium sulfate for 9.00 × 10<sup>3 </sup>s and found that 1.07 g of indium metal deposited on the cathode.</p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Calculate the charge, in coulombs, passed during the electrolysis.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\left( {{\\text{current }}I = \\frac{{{\\text{charge }}Q\\,}}{{{\\text{time }}t}}} \\right)\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>(</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>current </mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mi>I</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>charge </mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mi>Q</mi>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>time </mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mi>t</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mo>)</mo>\n</mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Calculate the amount, in mol, of electrons passed using section 2 of the data booklet.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Calculate the mass of indium deposited by one mole of electrons.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Calculate the number of moles of electrons required to deposit one mole of indium. Relative atomic mass of indium, <em>A</em><sub>r</sub>=114.82.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">d.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Deduce the charge on the indium ion and the formula of indium sulfate.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">e.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>«0.300A × 9.00 × 10<sup>3</sup> s =» 2.70 × 10<sup>3</sup> «C»</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>«mol e<sup>−</sup> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{2700\\,{\\text{C}}}}{{96\\,500\\,{\\text{C}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>2700</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>C</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>96</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mn>500</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>C</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>mo</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>l</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 2.80 × 10<sup>−2</sup> «mol»</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{1.07{\\rm{g}}}}{{0.0280{\\rm{mol}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1.07</mn>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0.0280</mn>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>=» 38.2 «g»</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{114.82\\,{\\text{g}}}}{{38.2\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>114.82</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>38.2</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>mo</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>l</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span> e<sup>−</sup> =» 3.01/3.00 «mol e<sup>−</sup>»</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">d.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>In<sup>3+</sup> /3+ <em><strong>AND</strong></em> In<sub>2</sub>(SO<sub>4</sub>)<sub>3</sub></p>\n<p><em>Do <strong>not</strong> accept “+3/3”</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">e.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">d.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">e.</div>\n</div>"}